  "commentary": "With SPX at 6602.7 sitting just below the massive +51947M gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that resistance zone while simultaneously buying weakness toward the 6590 negative gamma pocket. The 35-45% GEX decline signals rapid position unwinding, but the PIN regime with 108B+ total GEX should contain volatility and promote mean reversion between these key 6590-6605 boundaries. Watch for continued dealer selling pressure into 6605-6615 on any bounce attempts, while 6590 becomes the critical support where dealer buying should emerge.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590-6605 with dealers capping upside moves.",
